### CashFlow — REST Client requests
###
### Open this file in VS Code with the "REST Client" extension (humao.rest-client)
### or in JetBrains Rider. Each block separated by ### is executable.

@transactions = http://localhost:5001
@reporting    = http://localhost:5002
@merchant     = 11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111

### Health (Transactions)
GET {{transactions}}/health/ready

### Health (Reporting)
GET {{reporting}}/health/ready

### Register a credit transaction
# @name newCredit
POST {{transactions}}/api/v1/transactions
Content-Type: application/json
X-Correlation-Id: dev-{{$timestamp}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchant}}",
  "amount": 250.50,
  "type": "Credit",
  "description": "POS sale #042"
}

### Fetch the created transaction
GET {{transactions}}/api/v1/transactions/{{newCredit.response.body.id}}

### Register a debit transaction
POST {{transactions}}/api/v1/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchant}}",
  "amount": 80.00,
  "type": "Debit",
  "description": "Supplier payment"
}

### Invalid transaction (negative amount) → 422
POST {{transactions}}/api/v1/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchant}}",
  "amount": -50,
  "type": "Credit"
}

### Missing merchantId → 400 (FluentValidation)
POST {{transactions}}/api/v1/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "merchantId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "amount": 100,
  "type": "Credit"
}

### Daily balance for today (adjust the date as needed)
GET {{reporting}}/api/v1/daily-balance/{{merchant}}/2026-05-19

### Daily balance for a date with no data → 404
GET {{reporting}}/api/v1/daily-balance/{{merchant}}/2099-01-01
